						<div class="postbody">Or you could make the palette YUV (not HSV like on the NES), clock the DAC at 4*Fsc (14.32 MHz), and output Y+U, Y+V, Y-U, Y-V. Apple II uses something much like this.
<br />
<br />Once the prototype is working, the problem will become one of attracting developers and one of making enough units of your console to ship to customers.</div>

